## Architecture rules

- Business logic lives in `{{ path }}/services/`. API routes stay thin (validate input, call service, format response).
- All DB access goes through `{{ path }}/db/`. No raw SQL outside that boundary.
- Background work uses `{{ queue tool }}`. Do not add cron.
- Tenant scope is enforced at `{{ layer }}`. Every query that returns user data must include the tenant filter.

## What not to do

- Do not log secrets, payment payloads, or full request bodies. Use `{{ logger.redact(...) }}`.
- Do not introduce new top-level dependencies without listing them in the spec's Risks section first.
- Do not store IDs in memory across requests. Use the session/cache layer.
- Do not silently catch and re-throw. Either handle (with logged context) or let it propagate.

